%p.sg-p This project employs the <a class="sg-a" target="_blank" href="http://csswizardry.com/2012/06/single-direction-margin-declarations/">single-direction margining</a> technique throughout. Elements by default have a bottom margin of 20px and a top margin of 0. Last-child elements have a bottom margin of 0. If margining needs to be set on a new element or a default margin value needs to be overridden a number of spacing modifiers are available.

%table.sg-table
  %thead
    %tr
      %th Modifiers
      %th Descriptions
  %tbody
    - {'flush' => 0, 'small' => 10, 'normal' => 20, 'large' => 50}.each do |key, value|
      %tr
        %td 
          %span.sg-code .#{key}-bottom
        %td #{value}px bottom margin.
      - for bp in ['palm', 'lap', 'portable', 'desk']
        %tr
          %td 
            %span.sg-code .#{bp}--#{key}-bottom
          %td #{value}px bottom margin at the #{bp} breakpoint.
